# React Aria Components
[globs]: ["apps/builder/src/builder/components/**", "apps/builder/src/builder/panels/**"]
- All UI components must use React Aria for accessibility
- Use React-Aria hooks (useButton, useTextField, etc.) - no manual ARIA attributes
- Use React-Stately for state management (useToggleState, useListState, etc.)
- Use tv() from tailwind-variants for semantic class generation
- Ship with .stories.tsx for every new component

## CSS Class Naming (CRITICAL)
- **Always use `react-aria-*` prefix** (e.g., `react-aria-Button`, `react-aria-ComboBox`)
- Before creating new CSS, check `apps/builder/src/builder/components/styles/index.css`
- Reuse existing wrapper classes (e.g., `combobox-container`, `control-label`)

## Workflow for new Inspector components
1. Find closest React Aria component (ComboBox, Select, Input, etc.)
2. Read implementation in `apps/builder/src/builder/components/`
3. Copy className structure exactly
4. Reuse existing CSS - avoid creating new CSS files
